---
// Agentic AI narrative progression: Generative → Practical → Trusted → Agentic
---

<div class="ans-grid">
  <div class="ans-stage">
    <div class="ans-stage-header">
      <span class="ans-num">01</span>
      <h3 class="ans-title">Generative AI</h3>
    </div>
    <p class="ans-question">What can AI create?</p>
    <p class="ans-desc">The market question was possibility. Could AI write, summarise, translate, generate? The answer was yes — and it was faster and cheaper than expected. The editorial task was to calm the hype and give organisations practical guidance.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="ans-connector" aria-hidden="true">→</div>

  <div class="ans-stage">
    <div class="ans-stage-header">
      <span class="ans-num">02</span>
      <h3 class="ans-title">Practical AI</h3>
    </div>
    <p class="ans-question">How can businesses use it today?</p>
    <p class="ans-desc">The market question shifted to application. Not what AI could do in theory, but how it could be embedded into real business workflows. For finance, this meant domain-specific models — not general tools that could hallucinate in high-stakes contexts.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="ans-connector" aria-hidden="true">→</div>

  <div class="ans-stage">
    <div class="ans-stage-header">
      <span class="ans-num">03</span>
      <h3 class="ans-title">Trusted AI</h3>
    </div>
    <p class="ans-question">Can we trust it with data, decisions and workflows?</p>
    <p class="ans-desc">Governance, accuracy and appropriate use became market essentials. The argument shifted to Authentic Intelligence — AI capability built for a specific domain, with transparency about how it works and what it can be trusted to do.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="ans-connector" aria-hidden="true">→</div>

  <div class="ans-stage ans-stage--current">
    <div class="ans-stage-header">
      <span class="ans-num">04</span>
      <h3 class="ans-title">Agentic AI</h3>
    </div>
    <p class="ans-question">Can AI complete meaningful work on our behalf?</p>
    <p class="ans-desc">The market question is now execution. Agents that monitor, decide, draft and route across complex tasks continuously — not when prompted, but when something needs to happen. The shift is from hindsight to foresight.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
